            "kind": "narrator",
            "path": "/people/narrators/1",
            "text": "أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام )"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " قَالَ"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:63:2",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) إِنَّ أَبْغَضَ النَّاسِ إِلَى اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ رَجُلٌ جَرَّدَ ظَهْرَ مُسْلِمٍ بِغَيْرِ حَقٍّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘The most hateful of the people to Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic is a man who bares the back of a Muslim without a right (to do so)’."
        ]
      }
    },
